{
  "title": "Type-Checking Batch Jobs using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to implement type checking for batch jobs using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "Define Pydantic models for input and output data types",
    "Use Dependency injection to pass Pydantic models as dependencies to your batch functions",
    "Implement Async processing for handling multiple requests concurrently",
    "Utilize FastAPI's built-in features like validation, error handling, and documentation",
    "Leverage Python 3.12+'s improved type hinting and static analysis capabilities"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Depends\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\napp = FastAPI()\n\nclass InputData(BaseModel):\n    data: str\n\ndef batch_function(input_data: InputData) -> None:\n    # Your batch function implementation here\n\n@app.post('/batch/')\nasync def process_batch(input_data: InputData = Depends(InputData)):\n    await batch_function(input_data)\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for improved type hinting and static analysis capabilities.",
    "FastAPI version 0.70.0 or higher is recommended for this implementation."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Be aware that FastAPI doesn't support type checking for functions directly in the path operations.",
    "You may need to use third-party libraries like mypy or pyright for further static type checking."
  ]
}
